id: pm-2kkl
title: "GH-348: Windows nightly vitest worker fork exits unexpectedly during teardown (all 246/247 test files pass)"
description: "Nightly Validation windows-latest/Node20 fails with a single vitest 'Worker forks emitted error / Worker exited unexpectedly' unhandled error AFTER 246 of 247 test files pass (0 assertion failures). A worker process crashes during teardown, almost certainly a native resource (LanceDB or OTLP gRPC exporter) not releasing cleanly on Windows. Distinct symptom from pm-zpe7 (OTLP cleanup EBUSY) and pm-i84i (file:// TS import SyntaxError). Non-blocking for releases (auto-release green; npm 2026.6.23 published). Needs a Windows runner to reproduce/fix confidently; default vitest forks pool, no isolate/teardown override in vitest.config.ts."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 3
